class Solution:
    def largestMerge(self, word1: str, word2: str) -> str:
        merge = []
        while word1 and word2:
            if word1 > word2:
                merge.append(word1[0])
                word1 = word1[1:]
            else:
                merge.append(word2[0])
                word2 = word2[1:]

        # Append remaining characters from word1 or word2
        merge.append(word1)
        merge.append(word2)

        return ''.join(merge)
```

This solution works by comparing the remaining parts of `word1` and `word2` at each step and appending the larger starting character to the `merge` list. This ensures that the resulting merge is lexicographically largest. After one of the words is exhausted, the remaining part of the other word is appended to the result.
